### Set Domain Contacts [POST]

Updates the contacts for the domain. Pass a map of EPP contact type names
(e.g. `"registrant"`, `"admin"`, `"billing"`, `"tech"`) to contact data
objects in `contactIn` format.

The required `extension` fields depend on the domain's TLD and registry.

**Nominet** (`.uk`, `.co.uk`, `.me.uk`, `.org.uk`, etc.): `type` is required â€” accepted values are `IND`, `FIND`, `LTD`, `PLC`, `PTNR`, `LLP`, `SCH`, `RCHAR`, `GOV`, `CRC`, `STAT`, `OTHER`. `trad-name` sets a trading name and `co-no` sets the company number (ignored when `type` is `OTHER`).

**Titan** (`.ie`): `type` is required. `language` (uppercased) and `cro-number` are optional.

**Tucows/OpenSRS**: `type` is mapped per TLD â€” `.ca` â†’ `legal_type`; `.au`/`.com.au`/`.org.au` â†’ `eligibility_type` (also sets `registrant_name`); `.dk` â†’ `registrant_type` (normalised to `"individual"` or `"business"`); `.es` â†’ `es_id_type`; `.us` â†’ `app_purpose`; `.cl`, `.de`, `.fi`, `.hu`, `.lv`, `.mx`, `.my`, `.nu`, `.pt`, `.com.pt`, `.re`, `.ro`, `.com.ro`, `.se`, `.za`, `.co.za` â†’ `registrant_type`; all other Tucows TLDs â†’ `entity_type`. Additional optional fields: `language` (`lang`), `nationality-code`, `co-no`, `cro-number`, `fax`, `reg_code`, `country_of_citizenship`.

**CentralNic** â€” contacts are not supported; this endpoint returns `false`.

> **Note:** For `.uk` domains (Nominet), the registrant name (or organisation
> name if present) must match the existing record. If the names do not match,
> the update will be silently rejected and the method will return `false`.

```
    <?php
    $general_api_key = "API_KEY";
    $services_api = new \TwentyI\API\Services($general_api_key);

    $request = $services_api->postWithFields("/package/{packageId}/domain/{domainId}/contacts", [
            "(contact-type)" => []
    ]);
```
+ Parameters

    + packageId: 1 (number, required) - The Package ID retrieved from get packages.
    + domainId: 1 (number, required) - The domain ID retrieved from get domains.


+ Attributes

    
     
+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer token

    + Body

            {
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            
                true
            


