## Domain Names/Subdomains [/package/{packageId}/web/names]

### Add Names to a Package [POST]

Adds or removes domain names and subdomains from this web service.
Adding a name that already exists updates its document root path.

> **Note:** `add` accepts either a plain array of names or a map of
> `name => subdirectory` pairs. The `chg` field changes the primary name
> used for single-name functions such as the main FTP username.

```
    <?php
    $general_api_key = "API_KEY";
    $services_api = new \TwentyI\API\Services($general_api_key);

    $request = $services_api->postWithFields("/package/{packageId}/web/names", [
            "add" => ["string"],
            "rem" => ["string"],
            "chg" => "string"
    ]);
```
+ Parameters

    + packageId: 1 (number, required) - The Package ID retrieved from get packages.


+ Attributes

    + `add` (array[string],required) - Plain array of names, or a map of names to document root subdirectories {
    + `rem` (array[string],required) - Names to remove
    + `chg` (string,nullable) - The new primary name; defaults to the first name on the web
     
+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer token

    + Body

            {
                    add: ["string"],
                    rem: ["string"],
                    chg: "string"
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            
                ["string"]
            


