## StackCP Users [/reseller/{resellerId}/susers]

### Retrieve Stack User ConfigurationEach object includes lock references as keys, which further contain information such as IPv4 address, IPv6 address, and more.
           Each object includes service references as keys, indicating whether the service is granted to the user (true) or not (false).
                  Each object includes information about the service type and name.
       Each object represents a user and includes various identity-related information. [GET]

The "Retrieve Stack User Configuration" API endpoint allows you to retrieve your Stack user configuration. It returns various configuration settings associated with your Stack user account.

When making the API call, you need to provide the necessary parameters:

$args (optional): An array of arguments that can be passed to customize the retrieval of the Stack user configuration. It includes the following parameter:
topLevel (optional): If set to true, only top-level services will be returned.

The response from this API call will be an array containing the following information:

contact: An array representing the contact details associated with your Stack user. The array contains objects with user references as keys.
Each object includes information such as person name, company name, address, city, postal code, country code, voice (phone number), notes, billing reference, email, company number,
trading name, country alpha3 code, country alpha2 code, extended billing reference, and Nominet contact type.
ftpLock: An array representing FTP lock configurations. The array contains objects with user references as keys.
grant_map: An array representing the grant map of services. The array contains objects with user references as keys.
service_by_tuple: An array representing the service by tuple configuration. The array contains objects with service references as keys.
users: An array representing the users associated with your Stack account. The array contains objects with user references as keys.

Please note that this API endpoint is specifically related to StackCP users and is designed to provide access to your Stack user configuration within the 20i platform.
It allows you to retrieve and manage your user-related settings, contact details, FTP lock configurations, service grants, and more.

```
    <?php
    $general_api_key = "API_KEY";
    $services_api = new \TwentyI\API\Services($general_api_key);

    $request = $services_api->getWithFields("/reseller/{resellerId}/susers");
```
+ Parameters

    + resellerId: 1 (number, required) - Your reseller ID.



     
+ Request

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer token



+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            
                {
                    contact:{
                        (user_ref):{
                            person_name: "string",
                            company_name: "string",
                            address: "string",
                            city: "string",
                            sp: "string",
                            pc: "string",
                            cc: "string",
                            voice: "string",
                            notes: "string",
                            billing_ref: "string",
                            email: "string",
                            company_number: "string",
                            trading_name: "string",
                            ccAlpha3: "string",
                            ccAlpha2: "string",
                            ext_billing_ref: "string",
                            nominet_contact_type: "string"
                        }
                    },
                    ftpLock:{
                        (user_ref):{
                            (lock_ref):{
                                Ip4Address: "string",
                                Ip6Address: "string",
                            }
                        }
                    },
                    grant_map:{
                        (user_ref):{
                            (service_ref): true
                        }
                    },
                    service_by_tuple:{
                        (service_reference):{
                            serviceType: "string",
                            name: "string"
                        }
                    },
                    users:{
                        (user_ref):{
