### Create/Update a WordPress User [POST]

Sets users or creates a new one.
$user should be present if $type is create, otherwise null
$ID is required if $type is changePassword or remove
$password is required only if the $type is changePassword

```
    <?php
    $general_api_key = "API_KEY";
    $services_api = new \TwentyI\API\Services($general_api_key);

    $request = $services_api->postWithFields("/package/{packageId}/web/wordpressUsers", [
            "type" => "string",
            "user" => [
                "display_name" => "string",
                "user_email" => "string",
                "user_login" => "string",
                "password" => "string"
            ],
            "ID" => "string",
            "password" => "string"
    ]);
```
+ Parameters

    + packageId: 1 (number, required) - The Package ID retrieved from get packages.


+ Attributes

    + `type` (string,required) - one of create, changePassword, remove
    + `user` (object,nullable) - 
        - `display_name` (string,required) - 
        - `user_email` (string,required) - 
        - `user_login` (string,required) - 
        - `password` (string,required) - 
    + `ID` (string,nullable) - 
    + `password` (string,nullable) - 
     
+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer token

    + Body

            {
                    type: "string",
                    user:{
                        display_name: "string",
                        user_email: "string",
                        user_login: "string",
                        password: "string"
