+ Request

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer token



+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            
                {
                    countries: ["string"],
                    type: "string"
                }
            


### Set blocked countries [POST]

Sets the country blocking rule for this virtual host. Pass `allow` for
`access` to allow only the listed countries; any other value blocks them.
Pass an empty `countries` array to remove all country restrictions.

```
    <?php
    $general_api_key = "API_KEY";
    $services_api = new \TwentyI\API\Services($general_api_key);

    $request = $services_api->postWithFields("/package/{packageId}/web/blockedCountries", [
            "access" => "string",
            "countries" => ["string"]
    ]);
```
+ Parameters

    + packageId: 1 (number, required) - The Package ID retrieved from get packages.


+ Attributes

    + `access` (string,required) - Use `allow` to allow listed countries, or any other value to block them
    + `countries` (array[string],required) - ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country codes
     
+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer token

    + Body

            {
                    access: "string",
                    countries: ["string"]
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            
            


