# Group Managed VPS



## Activate/Deactivate managed vps [/managed_vps/{managedVpsId}/userStatus]

### Activate or deactivate [POST]

Activates or deactivates the service.
Possible subservice_name are 'default' for a typical set of services
and 'main' for the core service only.

```
    <?php
    $general_api_key = "API_KEY";
    $services_api = new \TwentyI\API\Services($general_api_key);

    $request = $services_api->postWithFields("/managed_vps/{managedVpsId}/userStatus", [
            "includeRepeated" => true,
            "subservices" => [
                "(subservice_name)" => true
            ]
    ]);
```
+ Parameters

    + managedVpsId: 1 (number, required) - The Managed VPS server ID retrieved from get managed vps.


+ Attributes

    + `includeRepeated` (boolean,required) - When reactivating, if true,this will revoke all your deactivations rather than
        just the current one.
    + `subservices` (object,required) - 
        - ``subservice_name`` (boolean,required) - True to enable, false to disable.
     
+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer token

    + Body

            {
                    includeRepeated: true,
                    subservices:{
                        (subservice_name): true
                    }
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            
                true
            


## Add Package [/managed_vps/{managedVpsId}/addWeb]

### Add a Package [POST]

Creates a new web hosting package on this Managed VPS under the specified domain name.

> **Note:** The domain name must be valid and not already assigned to another package under this account.

```
    <?php
    $general_api_key = "API_KEY";
    $services_api = new \TwentyI\API\Services($general_api_key);

    $request = $services_api->postWithFields("/managed_vps/{managedVpsId}/addWeb", [
            "domain_name" => "string",
            "extra_domain_names" => ["string"],
            "packageTemplate" => "string",
            "type" => 1
    ]);
```
+ Parameters

    + managedVpsId: 1 (number, required) - The Managed VPS server ID retrieved from get managed vps.


+ Attributes

    + `domain_name` (string,required) - The primary domain name for the new site
    + `extra_domain_names` (array[string],nullable) - Additional domain names to associate with the package
    + `packageTemplate` (string,nullable) - The domain name of an existing package to clone files and databases from
    + `type` (number,nullable) - The package bundle type ID to use (defaults to the reseller's Managed VPS type)
     
+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer token

    + Body

            {
                    domain_name: "string",
                    extra_domain_names: ["string"],
                    packageTemplate: "string",
                    type: 1
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            
                1
            


## Delete Package [/managed_vps/{managedVpsId}/deleteWeb]

### Delete a Package [POST]

Deletes one or more web hosting packages from this Managed VPS. Packages that have child sub-sites (sub-webs) are skipped and not deleted.

> **Warning:** Deleting a package permanently removes all associated files, databases, and configuration. This action cannot be undone.

```
    <?php
    $general_api_key = "API_KEY";
    $services_api = new \TwentyI\API\Services($general_api_key);

    $request = $services_api->postWithFields("/managed_vps/{managedVpsId}/deleteWeb", [
            "delete-id" => ["string"]
    ]);
```
+ Parameters

    + managedVpsId: 1 (number, required) - The Managed VPS server ID retrieved from get managed vps.


+ Attributes

    + `delete-id` (array[string],required) - Array of package IDs to delete
     
+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer token

    + Body

            {
                    delete-id: ["string"]
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            
                1
            


